Lagos State Government has reacted to a video showing kegs of petrol being distributed as souvenirs at a party. A statement on Saturday by Gbenga Omotoso Commissioner for Information described such as dangerous. The official said it was blatantly against all safety measures and could lead to the loss of lives and property. Omotoso announced that the authorities, through the Safety Commission, is investigating the matter. The commissioner vowed that all parties to the reprehensible act would be made to account for it. “The safety of lives and properties of Lagosians and visitors remains a top priority to the Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu administration. “We, therefore, advise that actions that can lead to loss of lives and properties be avoided”, the statement added.